# Build artifacts — see issue #16
# Precise patterns only; no aggressive globs (e.g. *.bin, cth/, cmd/*).

# Go test binaries (any package; produced by `go test -c` and `go test`)
*.test

# WASM build outputs (visualizer entrypoint)
cmd/wasm-visualizer/qbp.wasm

# Compiled CLI binaries (per-cmd, by exact name — leaves source dirs tracked)
cth/bin/
cmd/hw-eval/hw-eval

# Local worktrees (created via `git worktree add worktrees/<name> ...`).
# Untracked by policy — worktrees are forensic audit material per
# feedback_branch_cleanup.md (no pre-stable cleanup), not committable
# content. The single committed file under this path (worktrees/walk-
# infrastructure/pkg/gap/gap_gated.go, removed in v0.3 prereqs) was an
# initial-commit-era artifact pre-dating the worktrees pattern.
worktrees/
